                                 Q. What is flatMap(Function f) method ?
                                ===========================================
==> it is used to flaten list of streams into single stream....

package StreamAPIpkg;

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.stream.Stream;

public class flatMapDemo {

	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		List<String> javacourses = Arrays.asList("core java", "adv java", "spring boot");
		List<String> uicourses   = Arrays.asList("html", "css", "bs", "js");
		
		
		List<List<String>> courses = Arrays.asList(javacourses, uicourses);
		
		System.out.println("====without using flatmap==========");
		
		courses.stream().forEach(c -> System.out.println(c));
		
		
		System.out.println("=======using Flatmap()===============");
		//using flatmap
		
		Stream<String> fm = courses.stream().flatMap(s -> s.stream());
		fm.forEach(c -> System.out.println(c));
	}
}




======
OUTPUT:
======

====without using flatmap==========

[core java, adv java, spring boot]
[html, css, bs, js]

=======using Flatmap()===============
core java
adv java
spring boot
html
css
bs
js




                                ============================================================
                                        Slicing Operations with stream
                                ============================================================
=> distinct() --> To get unique elements from the stream..
=> limit(long maxSize) --> Get elements from the stream based on given size..
=> skip(long l) --> It is used to skip given number of elements from starting position of the stream...

Note: All the above three methods are comes under intermediate operational methods. They will perform operation and returns new stream.


example:
========


package StreamAPIpkg;

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.stream.Stream;

public class flatMapDemo {

	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		List<String> javacourses = Arrays.asList("core java", "adv java", "spring boot", "microservices");
		
		
		javacourses.stream().limit(3).forEach(c -> System.out.println(c));
		
		
		System.out.println("==========");
		
		javacourses.stream().skip(2).forEach(c -> System.out.println(c));
		
		System.out.println("==========");
		
		List<String> names = Arrays.asList("raja", "rani", "raja", "rani", "gopal");
		
		names.stream().distinct().forEach(c -> System.out.println(c));
		
	}
}


OUTPUT:
=======

core java
adv java
spring boot
==========
spring boot
microservices
==========
raja
rani
gopal






                                    =============================================
                                    Matching Operations with Stream
                                    =============================================

1. boolean anyMathc(Predicate p)
2. boolean allMatch(Predicate p)
3. boolean noneMatch(Predicate p)


Note: The above three methods are belongs to   Termnnal operation because they will do operations and they will return result directly(they won't return stream).

=> The above methods are used to check the given condition and returns true and false value based on condition.


Example for all 3 Matching Operations
=====================================


package StreamAPIpkg;

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class matchingCoceptDemo {

	
	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		Person p1 = new Person("john", "india");
		Person p2 = new Person("mohn", "canada");
		Person p3 = new Person("kohn", "bhutan");
		Person p4 = new Person("sohn", "india");
		Person p5 = new Person("horn", "india");
		
		
		List<Person> persons = Arrays.asList(p1,p2,p3,p4,p5);
		
		boolean status1 = persons.stream().anyMatch(p -> p.country.equals("india"));
		System.out.println("Any Indian Available ::" + status1);
		
		
		boolean status2 = persons.stream().anyMatch(p -> p.country.equals("canada"));
		System.out.println("Any canadian Available :: "+status2);
		
		boolean status3 = persons.stream().allMatch(p -> p.country.equals("austrelia"));
		System.out.println("Any austrelian Available :: "+status3);
		
		
		boolean status4 = persons.stream().noneMatch(p -> p.country.equals("maxico"));
		System.out.println("Any maxician available  :: " + status4);
		
	}
}


class Person{
	
	String name;
	String country;
	
	public Person(String name, String country) {

	
		this.name=name;
		this.country=country;
	
	}



OUTPUT:
=======

Any Indian Available ::true
Any canadian Available :: true
Any austrelian Available :: false
Any maxician available  :: true


                                                            
